GRID :
EX:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    <head>
        <title>grid</title>
        <style>
            body{
                margin: 0px;
                padding: 0px;
            }
            .parent{
                height: 100vh;
                display: grid;
                grid-template-rows: 15% 70% 15%;
                grid-template-columns: 15% 70% 15%;
            }
            .header{
                display: flex;
                justify-content: center;
                align-items: center;
                background-color: red;
                grid-row: 1/2;
                grid-column: 1/4;
            }
            .aside{
                display: flex;
                justify-content: center;
                align-items: center;
                background-color: blue;
                grid-row: 2/3;
                grid-column: 1/2;
            }
            .main{
                display: flex;
                justify-content: center;
                align-items: center;
                background-color: green;
                grid-row: 2/3;
                grid-column: 2/3;
            }
            .rightmenu{
                display: flex;
                justify-content: center;
                align-items: center;
                background-color: yellow;
                grid-row: 2/3;
                grid-column: 3/4;
            }
            .footer{
                display: flex;
                justify-content: center;
                align-items: center;
                background-color: orange;
                grid-row: 3/4;
                grid-column: 1/4;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <div class="parent">
            <div class="header">Header</div>
            <div class="aside">Aside</div>
            <div class="main">Main</div>
            <div class="rightmenu">Right Menu</div>
            <div class="footer">Footer</div>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>


Flex:
It is one dimensional
Directional
Display: flex;
It is easy and flexible to work
It has limited tools

Grid:
It is two dimensional
Directional
Display: grid;
It is complex but useful and powerful to work
It has advanced tools

Properties:

Display:grid;  - defines grid container
Grid-template-rows; - specifies how many rows in a web page and how much the each row is occupied 
Grid-template-columns; - specifies how many columns in a web page and how much the each column is occupied 
Grid-row; - specifies start and end of each row
Grid-column; - specifies start and end of each column





